        {
          "feedback": "The path `/login` tells the server which page is being requested. A phishing page can use a convincing path, so the key check here is the domain mismatch.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "Path"
        },
        {
          "feedback": "The query string can pass values like `next=/billing`, but it is not what identifies the site’s host. The safety concern comes from the domain not matching the expected company host.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "Query string"
        }
      ],
      "question": "Which URL part should be checked before signing in?"
    },
