{
  "situations": [
    {
      "dialogue": "Watch the red tape: it went up and down as the bump moved toward the wall, then the tape stayed on the same spot of the line. We need to explain what carried the disturbance.",
      "imagePrompt": "A taut rope tied to a wall, with a hand flicking one end. A single wave pulse is halfway along the rope. A red tape marker on the rope is shown moving up and down in place, with an arrow showing the pulse moving toward the wall.",
      "options": [
        {
